Summary: DONUTS ON A ROPE CONTRAIL-NEW ENGINE POPULSON SYSTEM
divs: Sighting DetailsTHE AIR FORCE IS WORKING ON A NEW TYPE OF POPULSON ENGINES. I HAVE READ ABOUT THIS NEW TYPE OF POPULSON, BUT FOR THE LIFE OF ME, I CAN'T REMEMBER WHAT IT IS CALLED ---SCRAM JET, RAM JET ????? FUEL TAKEN FROM ATMOSPHERE IN FLIGHT. WHEN RUNNING, IT MAKES A CONTRAIL THAT LOOKS LIKE DONUTS ON A ROPE OR SMOKE RINGS ON A STRING. THESE PLANES FLY VERY HIGH & VERY FAST !!
